# shadcn instructions

Use the latest version of Shadcn to install new components, like this command to add a button component:

```bash
pnpm dlx shadcn@latest add button
```

# drizzle entities and types

When creating new entities always add raw DB types (Select / Insert / Update) in `db/types.ts`.

# domain / view types

Composed types that extend or pick from DB types (e.g. with extra fields like `role`, nested relations, or picked subsets) belong in `src/types.ts`. Do NOT put them in the store or in component files.

# server functions

- **Components** – all `createServerFn` calls live in `actions.server.ts` inside the component's feature folder (e.g. `src/components/accounts/actions.server.ts`). Plain async helper functions called only from within server handlers (e.g. `requireOwner`) also live there — no need to wrap them in `createServerFn`.
- **Routes** – all `createServerFn` calls live in a sibling `*.server.ts` file next to the route (e.g. `src/routes/movements.server.ts`). If multiple child routes share a loader (e.g. `users.$id.ban.tsx`, `users.$id.delete.tsx`), extract it to a shared `users.$id.server.ts`.

# standard components rules

1. If adding Delete component, use `entityId` prop instead of `entity` prop, do not pass the whole entity object.
